title: Crash Victims Have Been Identified
content: Two people that died in a crash Tuesday night near Pierre have been identified by South Dakota Highway Patrol.   79-year-old James Schaefer, and 80-year-old Lois Zickrick both were thrown from the car when they were struck by another vehicle after failing to stop at a stop sign. Neither was wearing a seatbelt.    Hope Thompson, 18, was identified as the driver of the car that struck them. She along with two passengers were taken to the hospital in Chamberlain to be treated for minor injuries. All were released.    South Dakota Highway Patrol is still investigating the crash.    © 2018 KELOLAND TV. All Rights Reserved.
